Text: CLINTON: Tell me how it's affected you again.
Speech: Tell me how it's affected you again.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: CLINTON: You know people who've lost their jobs and lost their homes?
Speech: You know people who've lost their jobs and lost their homes?
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: CLINTON: Well, I've been governor of a small state for 12 years.
Speech: Well, I've been governor of a small state for 12 years.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I'll tell you how it's affected me.
Speech: I'll tell you how it's affected me.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Every year Congress and the president sign laws that make us do more things and gives us less money to do it with.
Speech: Every year Congress and the president sign laws that make us do more things and gives us less money to do it with.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I see people in my state, middle class people -- their taxes have gone up in Washington and their services have gone down while the wealthy have gotten tax cuts.
Speech: I see people in my state, middle class people -- their taxes have gone up in Washington and their services have gone down while the wealthy have gotten tax cuts.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I have seen what's happened in this last 4 years when -- in my state, when people lose their jobs there's a good chance I'll know them by their names.
Speech: I have seen what's happened in this last 4 years when -- in my state, when people lose their jobs there's a good chance I'll know them by their names.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: When a factory closes, I know the people who ran it.
Speech: When a factory closes, I know the people who ran it.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: When the businesses go bankrupt, I know them.
Speech: When the businesses go bankrupt, I know them.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And I've been out here for 13 months meeting in meetings just like this ever since October, with people like you all over America, people that have lost their jobs, lost their livelihood, lost their health insurance.
Speech: And I've been out here for 13 months meeting in meetings just like this ever since October, with people like you all over America, people that have lost their jobs, lost their livelihood, lost their health insurance.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: What I want you to understand is the national debt is not the only cause of that.
Speech: What I want you to understand is the national debt is not the only cause of that.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It is because America has not invested in its people.
Speech: It is because America has not invested in its people.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It is because we have not grown.
Speech: It is because we have not grown.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It is because we've had 12 years of trickle down economics.
Speech: It is because we've had 12 years of trickle down economics.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We've gone from first to twelfth in the world in wages.
Speech: We've gone from first to twelfth in the world in wages.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We've had 4 years where we've produced no private sector jobs.
Speech: We've had 4 years where we've produced no private sector jobs.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Most people are working harder for less money than they were making ten years ago.
Speech: Most people are working harder for less money than they were making ten years ago.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It is because we are in the grip of a failed economic theory.
Speech: It is because we are in the grip of a failed economic theory.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And this decision you're about to make better be about what kind of economic theory you want, not just people saying I'm going to go fix it but what are we going to do?
Speech: And this decision you're about to make better be about what kind of economic theory you want, not just people saying I'm going to go fix it but what are we going to do?
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I think we have to do is invest in American jobs, American education, control American health care costs and bring the American people together again.
Speech: I think we have to do is invest in American jobs, American education, control American health care costs and bring the American people together again.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: CLINTON: I think I remember the question.
Speech: I think I remember the question.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: (Laughter.)
Speech: (Laughter.)
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Let me say first of all, I want to answer your specific question but first of all, we all agree that there should be a growing economy.
Speech: Let me say first of all, I want to answer your specific question but first of all, we all agree that there should be a growing economy.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: What you have to decide is who's got the best economic plan.
Speech: What you have to decide is who's got the best economic plan.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And we all have ideas out there, and Mr. Bush has a record.
Speech: And we all have ideas out there, and Mr. Bush has a record.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: So I don't want you to read my lips and I sure don't want you to read his.
Speech: So I don't want you to read my lips and I sure don't want you to read his.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I do hope you will read our plans.
Speech: I do hope you will read our plans.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Now, specifically, one, on Medicare, it is not true that everyone knows how to fix it.
Speech: Now, specifically, one, on Medicare, it is not true that everyone knows how to fix it.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: There are different ideas -- the Bush plan, the Perot plan, the Clinton -- we have different ideas.
Speech: There are different ideas -- the Bush plan, the Perot plan, the Clinton -- we have different ideas.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I am convinced, having studied health care for a year hard and talking to hundreds and hundreds of people all across America, that you cannot control the cost of Medicare until you control the cost of private health care and public health care, with managed competition, ceiling on cost, and radical reorganization of the insurance markets.
Speech: I am convinced, having studied health care for a year hard and talking to hundreds and hundreds of people all across America, that you cannot control the cost of Medicare until you control the cost of private health care and public health care, with managed competition, ceiling on cost, and radical reorganization of the insurance markets.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: You've got to do that; we got to get those costs down.
Speech: You've got to do that; we got to get those costs down.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Number 2, with regard to Social Security, that program -- a lot of you may not know this -- it produces a $70 billion surplus a year.
Speech: Number 2, with regard to Social Security, that program -- a lot of you may not know this -- it produces a $70 billion surplus a year.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Social Security is in surplus $70 billion.
Speech: Social Security is in surplus $70 billion.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Six increases in the payroll tax -- that means people with incomes of $51,000 a year or less pay a disproportionally high share of the federal tax burden, which is why I want some middle-class tax relief.
Speech: Six increases in the payroll tax -- that means people with incomes of $51,000 a year or less pay a disproportionally high share of the federal tax burden, which is why I want some middle-class tax relief.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: What do we have to do?
Speech: What do we have to do?
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: By the time the century turns, we have got to have our deficit under control, we have to work out of so that surplus is building up so when the baby boomers like me retire, we're okay.
Speech: By the time the century turns, we have got to have our deficit under control, we have to work out of so that surplus is building up so when the baby boomers like me retire, we're okay.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Number 3, on the pension funds, I don't know as much about it, but I will say this.
Speech: Number 3, on the pension funds, I don't know as much about it, but I will say this.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: What I would do is to bring in the pension experts of the country, take a look at it, and strengthen the pension requirements further, because it's not just enough to have the guarantee.
Speech: What I would do is to bring in the pension experts of the country, take a look at it, and strengthen the pension requirements further, because it's not just enough to have the guarantee.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We had a guarantee on the S&Ls, right?
Speech: We had a guarantee on the S&Ls, right?
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We had a guarantee -- and what happened?
Speech: We had a guarantee -- and what happened?
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: You picked up a $500-billion bill because of the dumb way the federal government deregulated it.
Speech: You picked up a $500-billion bill because of the dumb way the federal government deregulated it.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: So I think we are going to have to change and strengthen the pension requirements on private retirement plans.
Speech: So I think we are going to have to change and strengthen the pension requirements on private retirement plans.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: CLINTON: I'd rather answer her question first and then I'll be glad to.
Speech: I'd rather answer her question first and then I'll be glad to.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Because the question you ask is important.
Speech: Because the question you ask is important.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: The end of the Cold War brings an incredible opportunity for change.
Speech: The end of the Cold War brings an incredible opportunity for change.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Winds of freedom blowing around the world, Russia demilitarizing.
Speech: Winds of freedom blowing around the world, Russia demilitarizing.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And it also requires us to maintain some continuity -- some bipartisan American commitment to certain principles.
Speech: And it also requires us to maintain some continuity -- some bipartisan American commitment to certain principles.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And I would just say there are three things that I would like to say -- number one -- we do have to maintain the world's strongest defense.
Speech: And I would just say there are three things that I would like to say -- number one -- we do have to maintain the world's strongest defense.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We may differ about what the elements of that are.
Speech: We may differ about what the elements of that are.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I think that defense needs to be -- with fewer people in permanent armed services but with greater mobility on the land, in the air and on the sea, with a real dedication to continuing development of high technology weaponry and well trained people.
Speech: I think that defense needs to be -- with fewer people in permanent armed services but with greater mobility on the land, in the air and on the sea, with a real dedication to continuing development of high technology weaponry and well trained people.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I think we're going to have to work to stop the proliferation of weapons of mass destruction.
Speech: I think we're going to have to work to stop the proliferation of weapons of mass destruction.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Got to keep going until all those nuclear weapons in Russia are gone and the other republics.
Speech: Got to keep going until all those nuclear weapons in Russia are gone and the other republics.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Number 2, if you don't rebuild the economic strength of this country at home, we won't be a superpower.
Speech: Number 2, if you don't rebuild the economic strength of this country at home, we won't be a superpower.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We can't have any more instances like what happened when Mr. Bush went to Japan and the Japanese prime minister said he felt sympathy for our country.
Speech: We can't have any more instances like what happened when Mr. Bush went to Japan and the Japanese prime minister said he felt sympathy for our country.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We have to be the strongest economic power in the world.
Speech: We have to be the strongest economic power in the world.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: That's what got me into this race, so we could rebuild the American economy.
Speech: That's what got me into this race, so we could rebuild the American economy.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And number three, we need to be a force for freedom and democracy and we need to use our unique position to support freedom, whether it's in Haiti or in China or in any other place, wherever the seeds of freedom are sprouting.
Speech: And number three, we need to be a force for freedom and democracy and we need to use our unique position to support freedom, whether it's in Haiti or in China or in any other place, wherever the seeds of freedom are sprouting.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We can't impose it, but we need to nourish it and that's the kind of thing that I would do as president -- follow those three commitments into the future.
Speech: We can't impose it, but we need to nourish it and that's the kind of thing that I would do as president -- follow those three commitments into the future.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: CLINTON: First of all, let me say that I've spent more of my time and life on this in the last 12 years than any other issue.
Speech: First of all, let me say that I've spent more of my time and life on this in the last 12 years than any other issue.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Seventy percent of my state's money goes to the public schools, and I was really honored when Time magazine said that our schools have shown more improvement than any other state in the country except one other -- they named 2 states showing real strides forward in the 80s.
Speech: Seventy percent of my state's money goes to the public schools, and I was really honored when Time magazine said that our schools have shown more improvement than any other state in the country except one other -- they named 2 states showing real strides forward in the 80s.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: So I care a lot about this, and I've spent countless hours in schools.
Speech: So I care a lot about this, and I've spent countless hours in schools.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: But let me start with what you said.
Speech: But let me start with what you said.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I agree with some of what Mr. Bush said, but it's nowhere near enough.
Speech: I agree with some of what Mr. Bush said, but it's nowhere near enough.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We live in a world where what you earn depends on what you can learn, where the average 18- year-old will change jobs 8 times in a lifetime and where none of us can promise any of you that what you now do for a living is absolutely safe from now on.
Speech: We live in a world where what you earn depends on what you can learn, where the average 18- year-old will change jobs 8 times in a lifetime and where none of us can promise any of you that what you now do for a living is absolutely safe from now on.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Nobody running can promise that, there's too much change in the world.
Speech: Nobody running can promise that, there's too much change in the world.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: So what should we do?
Speech: So what should we do?
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Let me reel some things off real quick, because you said you wanted specifics.
Speech: Let me reel some things off real quick, because you said you wanted specifics.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Number one, under my program we would provide matching funds to states to teach everybody with a job to read in the next 5 years and give everybody with a job the chance to get a high school diploma, in big places on the job.
Speech: Number one, under my program we would provide matching funds to states to teach everybody with a job to read in the next 5 years and give everybody with a job the chance to get a high school diploma, in big places on the job.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Number 2, we would provide 2-year apprenticeship programs to high school graduates who don't go to college.
Speech: Number 2, we would provide 2-year apprenticeship programs to high school graduates who don't go to college.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And community colleges are on the job.
Speech: And community colleges are on the job.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Number three, we'd open the doors to college education to high school graduates without regard to income.
Speech: Number three, we'd open the doors to college education to high school graduates without regard to income.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: They could borrow the money and pay it back as a percentage of their income or with a couple of years of service to our nation here at home.
Speech: They could borrow the money and pay it back as a percentage of their income or with a couple of years of service to our nation here at home.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Number 4, we would fully fund the Head Start program to get little kids off to a good start.
Speech: Number 4, we would fully fund the Head Start program to get little kids off to a good start.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And, 5, I would have an aggressive program of school reform, more choices -- I favor public schools or these new charter schools -- we can talk about that if you want.
Speech: And, 5, I would have an aggressive program of school reform, more choices -- I favor public schools or these new charter schools -- we can talk about that if you want.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I don't think we should spend tax money on private schools.
Speech: I don't think we should spend tax money on private schools.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: But I favor public school choice, and I favor radical decentralization in giving more power to better-trained principals and teachers with parent councils to control their schools.
Speech: But I favor public school choice, and I favor radical decentralization in giving more power to better-trained principals and teachers with parent councils to control their schools.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Those things would revolutionize American education and take us to the top economically.
Speech: Those things would revolutionize American education and take us to the top economically.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: CLINTON: In 6 years -- I budget all this in my budget, and in 6 years the college program would cost 8 billion dollars over and above what -- the present student loan program costs 4; you pay 3 billion dollars for busted loans, because we don't have an automatic recovery system, and a billion dollars in bank fees.
Speech: In 6 years -- I budget all this in my budget, and in 6 years the college program would cost 8 billion dollars over and above what -- the present student loan program costs 4; you pay 3 billion dollars for busted loans, because we don't have an automatic recovery system, and a billion dollars in bank fees.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: So the net cost would be 8 billion 6 years from now in a trillion-plus budget -- not very much.
Speech: So the net cost would be 8 billion 6 years from now in a trillion-plus budget -- not very much.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: The other stuff -- all the other stuff I mentioned -- costs much less than that.
Speech: The other stuff -- all the other stuff I mentioned -- costs much less than that.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: The Head Start program full funding would cost about 5 billion more.
Speech: The Head Start program full funding would cost about 5 billion more.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And it's all covered in my budget from -- the plans that I've laid out -- from raising taxes on families with incomes above $200,000 and asking foreign corporations to pay the same tax that American corporations do on the same income, from $140 billion in budget cuts, including what I think are very prudent cuts in the defense budget.
Speech: And it's all covered in my budget from -- the plans that I've laid out -- from raising taxes on families with incomes above $200,000 and asking foreign corporations to pay the same tax that American corporations do on the same income, from $140 billion in budget cuts, including what I think are very prudent cuts in the defense budget.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It's all covered in the plan.
Speech: It's all covered in the plan.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: CLINTON: I just want to mention if I could --
Speech: I just want to mention if I could --
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Including the parents in the preschool education of their kids, even if they're poor and uneducated, can make a huge difference.
Speech: Including the parents in the preschool education of their kids, even if they're poor and uneducated, can make a huge difference.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We have a big program in my state that teaches mothers or fathers to teach their kids to get ready for school.
Speech: We have a big program in my state that teaches mothers or fathers to teach their kids to get ready for school.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It's the most successful thing we've ever done.
Speech: It's the most successful thing we've ever done.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Just a fact clarification real quickly.
Speech: Just a fact clarification real quickly.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We do not spend a higher percentage of our income on public education than every other country.
Speech: We do not spend a higher percentage of our income on public education than every other country.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: There are 9 countries that spend more than we do on public education.
Speech: There are 9 countries that spend more than we do on public education.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We spend more on education 'cause we spend so much more on colleges.
Speech: We spend more on education 'cause we spend so much more on colleges.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: But if you look at public education alone and you take into account the fact that we have more racial diversity and more poverty, it makes a big difference.
Speech: But if you look at public education alone and you take into account the fact that we have more racial diversity and more poverty, it makes a big difference.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: There are great public schools where there's public school choice, accountability and brilliant principals.
Speech: There are great public schools where there's public school choice, accountability and brilliant principals.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I'll just mention one -- the Beasley Academic Center in Chicago.
Speech: I'll just mention one -- the Beasley Academic Center in Chicago.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I commend it to anybody.
Speech: I commend it to anybody.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It's as good as any private school in the country.
Speech: It's as good as any private school in the country.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: CLINTON: Well, I don't have any idea but I hope it will happen some time in my lifetime.
Speech: Well, I don't have any idea but I hope it will happen some time in my lifetime.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: CLINTON: I believe that this country is electing more and more African Americans and Latinos and Asian Americans who are representing districts that are themselves not necessarily of a majority of their race.
Speech: I believe that this country is electing more and more African Americans and Latinos and Asian Americans who are representing districts that are themselves not necessarily of a majority of their race.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: The American people are beginning to vote across racial lines, and I hope it will happen more and more.
Speech: The American people are beginning to vote across racial lines, and I hope it will happen more and more.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: More and more women are being elected.
Speech: More and more women are being elected.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Look at all these women Senate candidates we have here.
Speech: Look at all these women Senate candidates we have here.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And you know, according to my mother and my wife and my daughter, this world would be a lot better place if women were running it most of the time.
Speech: And you know, according to my mother and my wife and my daughter, this world would be a lot better place if women were running it most of the time.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I do think there are special experiences and judgments and backgrounds and understandings that women bring to this process, by the way.
Speech: I do think there are special experiences and judgments and backgrounds and understandings that women bring to this process, by the way.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: This lady said here, how have you been affected by the economy.
Speech: This lady said here, how have you been affected by the economy.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I mean, women know what's it like to be paid an unequal amount for equal work.
Speech: I mean, women know what's it like to be paid an unequal amount for equal work.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: They know what it's like not to have flexible working hours.
Speech: They know what it's like not to have flexible working hours.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: They know what it's like not to have family leave or childcare.
Speech: They know what it's like not to have family leave or childcare.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: So I think it would be a good thing for America if it happened.
Speech: So I think it would be a good thing for America if it happened.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And I think it will happen in my lifetime.
Speech: And I think it will happen in my lifetime.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: CLINTON: Thank you, Carole, and thank you, ladies and gentlemen.
Speech: Thank you, Carole, and thank you, ladies and gentlemen.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Since I suggested this format I hope it's been good for all of you.
Speech: Since I suggested this format I hope it's been good for all of you.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I really tried to be faithful to your request that we answer the questions specifically and pointedly.
Speech: I really tried to be faithful to your request that we answer the questions specifically and pointedly.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I thought I owed that to you and I respect you for being here and for the impact you've had on making this a more positive experience.
Speech: I thought I owed that to you and I respect you for being here and for the impact you've had on making this a more positive experience.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: These problems are not easy.
Speech: These problems are not easy.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: They're not going to be solved overnight.
Speech: They're not going to be solved overnight.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: But I want you to think about just 2 or 3 things.
Speech: But I want you to think about just 2 or 3 things.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: First of all, the people of my state have let me be their governor for 12 years because I made commitments to 2 things -- more jobs and better schools.
Speech: First of all, the people of my state have let me be their governor for 12 years because I made commitments to 2 things -- more jobs and better schools.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Our schools are now better.
Speech: Our schools are now better.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Our children get off to a better start from pre-school programs and smaller classes in the early grades, and we have one of the most aggressive adult education programs in the country.
Speech: Our children get off to a better start from pre-school programs and smaller classes in the early grades, and we have one of the most aggressive adult education programs in the country.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We talked about that.
Speech: We talked about that.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: This year my state ranks first in the country in job growth, 4th in manufacturing in job growth, 4th in income growth, 4th in the decline of poverty.
Speech: This year my state ranks first in the country in job growth, 4th in manufacturing in job growth, 4th in income growth, 4th in the decline of poverty.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I'm proud of that.
Speech: I'm proud of that.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It happened because I could work with people -- Republicans and Democrats.
Speech: It happened because I could work with people -- Republicans and Democrats.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: That's why we've had 24 retired generals and admirals, hundreds of business people, many of them Republican, support this campaign.
Speech: That's why we've had 24 retired generals and admirals, hundreds of business people, many of them Republican, support this campaign.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: You have to decide whether you want to change or not.
Speech: You have to decide whether you want to change or not.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We do not need 4 more years of an economic theory that doesn't work.
Speech: We do not need 4 more years of an economic theory that doesn't work.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We've had 12 years of trickle down economics.
Speech: We've had 12 years of trickle down economics.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It's time to put the American people first, to invest and grow this economy.
Speech: It's time to put the American people first, to invest and grow this economy.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I'm the only person here who's ever balanced a government budget and I've presented 12 of them and cut spending repeatedly.
Speech: I'm the only person here who's ever balanced a government budget and I've presented 12 of them and cut spending repeatedly.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: But you cannot just get there by balancing the budget.
Speech: But you cannot just get there by balancing the budget.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We've got to grow the economy by putting people first -- real people like you.
Speech: We've got to grow the economy by putting people first -- real people like you.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I got into this race because I did not want my child to grow up to be part of the first generation of Americans to do worse than her parents.
Speech: I got into this race because I did not want my child to grow up to be part of the first generation of Americans to do worse than her parents.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We're better than that.
Speech: We're better than that.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We can do better than that.
Speech: We can do better than that.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I want to make America as great as it can be and I ask for your help in doing it.
Speech: I want to make America as great as it can be and I ask for your help in doing it.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Thank you very much.
Speech: Thank you very much.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton
